Looking to update your summer wardrobe and show off your love of fast food at the same time? Well, McDonald’s might just have the garments for you. The eatery chain is giving away a total of 1,000 limited-edition summer shirts for free. There are three designs, inspired by their iconic Big Macs, milkshake cups and fries, and they come in sizes small, medium, large and extra-large. The giveaway is now live, with a branded Facebook post explaining that you have until 23:59 on July 5 to enter for a chance to win one. All you need to do is check out the post, click ‘Learn More’ and type in your details. You’ve got to be over 18 to enter, and all shirts will be received within 28 days of notification that you’ve won one. The post reads: ‘It’s time to roll out the red carpet for lucky brand fans. ‘Looking for a unique way to be spotted this summer? Then it could be your lucky day.’ McDonald’s is also offering a summer menu for a limited time, with a taste of Italy menu available till the July 26, followed by a taste of Spain and Cyprus from the July 27 to September 6. The menus include: Taste of Italy Menu Taste of Spain and Cyprus Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk MORE : McDonald’s burger with ‘only ketamine’ label delivered to hungover student MORE : From McDonalds to Burger King and KFC: We rank the best plant-based burgers on the market MORE : McDonald’s agrees to pay £1,000,000,000 to avoid tax evasion trial